That's React.

Rule #10

Master Arrays.

React lives inside arrays.

You should know these by heart.

map()

Think

Every item

↓

Do something
Apple

Banana

Orange

↓

🍎

🍌

🍊

React

Links

↓

Cards
filter()

Think

Keep only matches
Google

Facebook

GitHub

Search

git

↓

GitHub
find()

Think

First match

Used for

Edit

findIndex()

Think

Where is it?

Returns

0

1

2

3
some()

Think

Does ANY match?

Returns

true

false
every()

Think

Do ALL match?

Returns

true

false
Rule #11

Local Storage is just a cupboard.

React

↓

puts data

↓

Cupboard

↓

Close browser

↓

Open browser

↓

Take data back

That's it.

Rule #12

JSON is a translator.

React understands

Objects

Local Storage understands

Strings

JSON translates.

Object

↓

JSON.stringify()

↓

String

Back

String

↓

JSON.parse()

↓

Object
Rule #13

Every React app asks four questions.

What data?

↓

Interface

Where is the data?

↓

State

Who owns it?

↓

Parent

Who displays it?

↓

Child

If you answer those...

You can build almost anything.

Rule #14

Components are LEGO bricks.

Don't build

Huge App

Build

Header

↓

Search

↓

Form

↓

Card

↓

Footer

Small pieces.

Rule #15

The Golden Rule

Never ask

"How do I build this app?"

Instead ask

What data?

↓

Who owns it?

↓

Who displays it?

↓

How does it change?

That's React thinking.
